      "date": "2017-11-30 16:32:52.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> Jinshan, is is_bl_done is moved upper, do we still need it in\n > ldlm_cancel_callback() ? iirc, it was introduced to protect\n > cleanup_resource vs bl thread race, because the clearup_resource\n > does not pass the async flag down; it is covered by the upper check\n > now.\n\nProbably the 'ldlm_is_bl_done()' branch in 'ldlm_cancel_callback()' is no longer needed because after this change is introduced only one thread can enter into lock cancellation code.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
