      "date": "2017-11-30 21:28:28.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nthe last point made by Mike regarding the cancel_on_bock is valid, but does not happen in reality as it seems to be used only for flocks now which do not use this blocking code. however, it would be better to land a clean code, either by adding this logic (removing that extra set_cancel?) or even preferably by moving the whole is_bl_done logic to ldlm_cli_cancel",
